{"cursor":"3163","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Substitution' is a fundamental concept in logic. Substitution is a syntactic\ntransformation on strings of symbols of a formal language.\n\nIn propositional logic, a 'substitution instance' of a propositional formula is\na second formula obtained by replacing symbols of the original formula by other\nformulas. For any formal system that is [[deductive closure|closed]] under\nsubstitution, any substitution of a tautology will also produce a tautology.\n","linknr":414,"url":"Substitution_(logic)","recorded":1362688560,"links":13,"instances":["formal","computer_science","computer_science","logic","logic","logic","logic"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Propositional calculus","Concepts in logic","Logical truth","Automated theorem proving","Logic programming"],"headings":["Definition","Tautologies","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/math/1/b/1/1b18a4c4fc578ef4cfd1cc0eb0daa473.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/1/b/1/1b18a4c4fc578ef4cfd1cc0eb0daa473.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/1/b/1/1b18a4c4fc578ef4cfd1cc0eb0daa473.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/1/b/1/1b18a4c4fc578ef4cfd1cc0eb0daa473.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/c/c/0cc175b9c0f1b6a831c399e269772661.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/c/c/0cc175b9c0f1b6a831c399e269772661.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/c/c/0cc175b9c0f1b6a831c399e269772661.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/c/c/0cc175b9c0f1b6a831c399e269772661.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["syntax","logic"],["string","computer_science"],["symbol","formal"],["tautology","logic"],["tautology","logic"],["valuation","logic"],["interpretation","logic"],["equality","mathematics#some_basic_logical_properties_of_equality"],["unification","computer_science"]],"members":["equalit